HEADWORD: Decollated
<hw>De*col"la*ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Decapitated; worn or cast off in the process of growth, as the apex
of certain univalve shells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decollation</ent>⟦br⟧
